The paper deals with finding complex activities in surveillance videos, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel framework for learning and retrieving activity graphs, which involves probabilistic modeling and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with information retrieval and search algorithms, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves processing and analyzing multimedia data, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
